reviewText: I just want to know if this last season will go until the fight between Yugi and Yami Yugi, the episode 224? Thanks

I loved this show since it first premiered on kids Wb and I sometimes missed episodes but now I can own them all and catch up on the ones I missed and re-watch ones I loved the most. After the show is finished being released I Hope GX gets a box set release and New Video can get a company to dub the remaining episodes so we can have the whole series in english and on dvd.
I believe the final case cover should have Red Eyes Black Dragon on it since seasons one- four have Blue Eyes White Dragon, Dark Magician, Dark Pladin, and Dark Magician Girl respectively.

I expect this set to be like the others. A cardboard slipcase, 2 DVD cases with 3-4 DVDs each. With some cool designs on the covers of each. It's the 4Kids dub, but what can you do. Hopefully once they get this out, they'll start releasing GX & 5Ds, with finished dubs for the episodes 4Kids didn't do. I'll update this review once I get the set.

Maybe after this final Season, they will start the same thing with Yu-gi-oh! GX and hopefully create DVDS not just for the first Season, but also Season 2, 3, and maybe have Season 4 in English Audio as well.

With Season 5, the story is now complete and so is the collection of this amazing serie and wonderful DVD-boxes!

I have FINALLY completed collecting all 5 seasons of Yu-Gi-Oh! Which has been something I've wanted to do since I was little. Forgot how much I truly loved this anime until I watched it all the way through.

I bought this season because it is the last season of the Series Yu-Gi-Oh! I also have the previous 4 seasons & I wanted to complete my collection. It was also nice to watch the final duel especially between Yugi & Atem (The Pharaoh) again. That was a terrific duel.

This is it, the final season of Yugioh. In this season, we experience Atem's past about the hellish war between Atem and the darkness in ancient Egypt, and the devastating power of the Egyptian Gods. This season takes place after Atem, Kaiba, and Joey defeated Dartz and Kaiba sets up a tournament in the first half and in the last half is Atem's past also the most sad and memorial moment of all Yugioh fandom: the final duel between Atem and Yugi. The final duel will determine Atem's fate if he can stay with Yugi or vanish with his friends forever. I hope New Video Group will release GX, and 5D's in the future.

I'm glad to finally complete my entire yugioh collection. I'm more excited that the GRAND CHAMPIONSHIP & DAWN OF THE DUEL will finally be together as one. What I'm NOT excited about is this price. $50???...really???...I shop on amazon at least once a week & usually they have the better price, but not this time. I found this elsewhere for HALF the price. amazon dropped the ball on this one.

Let's hope that Cinedigm (who now own New Video Group) don;t stop here, but go on to release GX, 5DS and Zexal. Espescially if they can dub the missing episodes.

The Cinedigm release that announced the partnership with 4Kids stated that the deal covered "600 episodes" which is, of course, far more than the original series and than we have seen on DVD thusfar, so it is quite likely it seems that the sequel series are destined for release also.

The release rate is quite fast too, thankfuly nothing like the other studios like Fox who have in th epast taken years between half-seasons and who even now release the Simpons slower than it;s being made/broadcast!

I would love this to be released in the UK badly cause i don't want to buy in volumes :(
